    "Larger Players Gain More From AlgorithmsIf efficiency improvements are scale-dependent, then algorithmic progress have not been uniform across small and large algorithmic providers.",
    "Model trainers with a large computational budget see much greater improvements with the introduction of new algorithms than smaller builders.",
    "Model builders scaling at the frontier see gains in the tens of thousands, while smaller model builders see algorithmic progress at levels much more similar to hardware progress.",
    "This mimics progress in traditional algorithms as seen in Sherry and Thompson [2021].",
    "This means that new architectures or scaling paradigms could accelerate rather than reduce inequality between model producers."
